I’ve confirmed the zero-supply reset exists exactly as reported. The open question is harm model: outstanding borrows can’t normally coexist with `totalSupply == 0` because the final redemption is cash-gated, but unsolicited underlying that lands after supply hits zero is still claimable by the next minter. That supports a downgraded, lower-confidence value-capture finding rather than the stronger “future repayments” variant.
